text.tspan: The Living Planet Index (LPI) measures the average decline in monitored wildlife populations. The index value is
measured relative to 20,811 populations of 4,392 species in 1970 (i.e. 1970 = 100%).
Source: Living Planet Report (2020). World Wildlife Fund (WWF) and Zoological Society of London.
